### English Title:
Houthi Forces Shoot Down Fifth U.S. Drone in Yemen Amid Ongoing Military Campaign

### English Text Summary:
On Friday, Houthi forces in Yemen shot down a U.S. MQ9 Reaper drone, marking the fifth drone downed since the U.S. expanded its military campaign against the group on March 15. This incident brings the total to six drones shot down since March 3. Each drone costs approximately $30 million, and the U.S. has just over 200 advanced drones in its arsenal. Despite over a month of daily U.S. airstrikes against the Houthis, the group continues to launch ballistic missiles at Israel and down U.S. drones used for surveillance in Yemen. The military campaign has reportedly cost around $1 billion in the first three weeks but has had limited impact. The Houthis are fortifying their military positions underground, even as the U.S. employs B2 bombers from Diego Garcia to target them.

